Androconia : Sdb HWD compact, dark brown to blackish, Sdp HWD fat lenticular, black, CuA 2 inflated vein narrowly swollen to about 2 /3, 1A+ 2 A vein also inflated. The degree of HW inflation may be variable, but these veins do not exhibit discrete ‘balloons’ (swellings);
Lees ( 1997 : 96 )
showed for one specimen that the veins that were significantly inflated along their length comprised only M 3 for the medial system.
